CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 26, 1959, p. A3, reads: "BEAUTIFUL LOUNGE - At left is the lounge of the New Loendi, with marble fireplace, planter box, and part of the lobby. The logs were designed by Commander Brown (now retired) whose log business has been known from coast to coast... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Lounge of Loendi Club with linoleum floor, fireplace with mirror, sofas, lamps, room divider on track, planter, paintings, including reproduction of Pieter Bruegel painting "The Hunters in the Snow", and exit sign
